you count, Mrs. Bundy?

953
01:18:53,927 --> 01:18:57,090
Which gulls, Mr. Sholes?
There are several varieties.

954
01:18:57,197 --> 01:18:59,495
The ones who've been
playing devil with my fishing boats.

955
01:18:59,533 --> 01:19:02,502
- Have you had trouble with gulls?
- One of my boats did, last week.

956
01:19:02,603 --> 01:19:05,401
This young lady was hit
by a gull only Saturday.

957
01:19:05,506 --> 01:19:08,907
Deke, I'm still waiting for
those Bloody Marys. Comin'right up.

958
01:19:09,009 --> 01:19:11,204
Could you ask them
to lower their voices,

959
01:19:11,311 --> 01:19:13,336
please? They're
frightening the children.

960
01:19:13,447 --> 01:19:16,109
A whole flock of gulls
nearly capsized one of my boats.

961
01:19:16,216 --> 01:19:18,116
Practically tore the skipper's arm off.

962
01:19:18,218 --> 01:19:20,812
You're scaring the
kids. Keep it low. All right.

963
01:19:20,921 --> 01:19:23,719
Yeah, but he's scarin' me, too.

964
01:19:23,757 --> 01:19:26,225
Are you tryin' to say that all these...

965
01:19:27,661 --> 01:19:29,629
Nah, that sounds impossible, Sebastian.

966
01:19:29,663 --> 01:19:32,427
Deke, look, I'm just tellin' you
what happened to one of my boats.

967
01:19:32,533 --> 01:19:35,229
The gulls were after
your fish, Mr. Sholes.

968
01:19:35,269 --> 01:19:37,635
Really, let's be logical about this.

969
01:19:37,738 --> 01:19:39,968
What were the crows after at the school?

970
01:19:41,942 --> 01:19:44,137
What do you think they
were after? Miss, uh...

971
01:19:44,177 --> 01:19:46,975
Daniels. I think they
were after the children.

972
01:19:47,080 --> 01:19:51,346
- For what purpose?
- To kill them.

973
01:19:51,385 --> 01:19:55,685
- Why?
- I don't know why.

974
01:19:55,756 --> 01:19:59,157
I thought not. Birds have
been on this planet, Miss Daniels,

975
01:19:59,192 --> 01:20:02,958
Since archeopteryx,
140 million years ago.

976
01:20:02,996 --> 01:20:06,056
Doesn't it seem odd that
they'd wait all that time...

977
01:20:06,166 --> 01:20:08,794
to start a... a war against humanity?

978
01:20:08,902 --> 01:20:11,302
No one called it a war.
Scotch, light on the water.

979
01:20:11,371 --> 01:20:14,272
You and Mr. Sholes
seem to be implying as much.

980
01:20:14,308 --> 01:20:17,106
Who said anything about a
war? All I said, some gulls...

981
01:20:17,177 --> 01:20:19,111
Want some more coffee? No.

982
01:20:19,179 --> 01:20:21,113
...came down on one of my boats.

983
01:20:21,181 --> 01:20:23,376
They could have been after
the fish, just like you said.

984
01:20:23,417 --> 01:20:26,215
- The Captain should have shot at them.
- Huh?

985
01:20:26,320 --> 01:20:29,778
Gulls are scavengers,
anyway. Most birds are.

986
01:20:29,890 --> 01:20:32,415
Get yourselves guns and wipe
them off the face of the Earth!

987
01:20:32,526 --> 01:20:36,519
That would hardly be possible.
- Why not, Mrs. Bundy?

988
01:20:36,597 --> 01:20:39,998
Because there are 8,650 species...

989
01:20:40,100 --> 01:20:42,796
of birds in the world today, Mr. Carter.

990
01:20:42,903 --> 01:20:46,737
It is estimated that
5,750,000,000 birds...

991
01:20:46,807 --> 01:20:48,741
live in the United States alone.

992
01:20:48,809 --> 01:20:50,743
The five continents of the world...

993
01:20:50,811 --> 01:20:53,609
Kill 'em all. Get
rid of the messy animals.

994
01:20:53,647 --> 01:20:56,741
...probably contain
more than 100 billion birds.

995
01:20:56,783 --> 01:20:58,307
It's the end of the world.

996
01:20:58,352 --> 01:21:00,547
- Those gulls must
have been after the fish

997
01:21:00,587 --> 01:21:03,488
Of course! Hurry up,
children. Finish your lunch.

998
01:21:03,557 --> 01:21:06,253
Are the birds gonna eat us, Mommy?

999
01:21:06,360 --> 01:21:09,090
Hell, maybe we're all getting
a little carried away by this.

1000
01:21:09,162 --> 01:21:10,857
Admittedly, a few birds did act strange,

1001
01:21:10,964 --> 01:21:12,556
but that's no reason to believe that...

1002
01:21:12,599 --> 01:21:16,763
I keep telling you, this isn't a few
birds. These are gulls, crows, swifts...

1003
01:21:16,870 --> 01:21:20,067
I have never known birds of
different species to flock together.

1004
01:21:20,173 --> 01:21:22,664
The very concept is unimaginable.

1005
01:21:22,776 --> 01:21:25,973
Why, if that happened,
we wouldn't have a chance!

1006
01:21:26,079 --> 01:21:28,309
How could we
possibly hope to fight them?

1007
01:21:28,382 --> 01:21:31,476
We couldn't, you're
right. You're right, Mrs. Bundy.

1008
01:21:31,585 --> 01:21:33,416
What's the matter?
Somethin' wrong out here?

1009
01:21:33,520 --> 01:21:35,010
- We're fighting a war, Sam

1010
01:21:35,122 --> 01:21:37,386
A war? Against who?

1011
01:21:37,424 --> 01:21:38,982
Against birds!

1012
01:21:39,026 --> 01:21:41,517
- I'm glad you all
think this is so amusing

1013
01:21:41,595 --> 01:21:44,792
You've frightened the children half out
of their wits. If the young lady said...

1014
01:21:44,898 --> 01:21:47,833
she saw the attack at a
school, why don't you believe her?

1015
01:21:47,934 --> 01:21:50,835
What attack? Who attacked
the school? Birds did. Crows.

1016
01:21:50,937 --> 01:21:53,303
You're all sitting around here debating!

1017
01:21:53,407 --> 01:21:55,739
What do you want them to do
next? Crash through that window?

1018
01:21:55,776 --> 01:21:59,872
Mommy! Ssh. Put on your coat.

1019
01:22:00,347 --> 01:22:03,578
Why don't you all go home,
lock your doors and windows?

1020
01:22:03,684 --> 01:22:05,549
What's the fastest way to San Francisco?

1021
01:22:05,652 --> 01:22:07,142
- The freeway, ma'am

1022
01:22:07,254 --> 01:22:08,744
How do I find it?

1023
01:22:08,855 --> 01:22:11,380
- I'm goin'out that
way, lady. You can follow me

1024
01:22:11,491 --> 01:22:15,450
- Well then, let's leave now.
- Haven't finished my drink yet.

1025
01:22:16,063 --> 01:22:18,463
I got here as fast as
I could. Where's Cathy?

1026
01:22:18,498 --> 01:22:21,399
She's with Annie. She's all right.
Al, why aren't you over at the school,

1027
01:22:21,501 --> 01:22:22,991
Where the attack was?

1028
01:22:23,103 --> 01:22:25,298
- 'Cause I just got
back from Dan Fawcett's place

1029
01:22:25,372 --> 01:22:28,603
- He was killed last night by birds.
- What?

1030
01:22:28,709 --> 01:22:30,700
Hold it, you don't know that for a fact.

1031
01:22:30,777 --> 01:22:32,301
What are the facts?

1032
01:22:32,379 --> 01:22:35,576
- The Santa Rosa Police
think it's a felony murder

1033
01:22:35,615 --> 01:22:37,583
They think a burglar
broke in and killed him.

1034
01:22:37,617 --> 01:22:39,778
How do they explain the
dead birds all over the floor?

1035
01:22:39,886 --> 01:22:43,185
Santa Rosa Police figure they
got in after the old man was killed.

1036
01:22:43,223 --> 01:22:45,783
Were the Santa Rosa
Police at your school today?

1037
01:22:45,826 --> 01:22:48,795
- Are you coming?
- Now take it easy, lady.

1038
01:22:48,829 --> 01:22:51,389
There isn't a bird anywhere in sight!

1039
01:22:51,498 --> 01:22:55,127
"Look at the birds of the
air. They do not sow or reap.

1040
01:22:55,235 --> 01:22:58,932
Yet your Heavenly Father feeds them."

1041
01:22:58,972 --> 01:23:01,770
Something like this
happened in Santa Cruz last year.

1042
01:23:01,875 --> 01:23:04,673
The town was just covered with seagulls.

1043
01:23:04,745 --> 01:23:08,340
- Please finish your drink.
- That's right, sir. I recall it.

1044
01:23:08,381 --> 01:23:10,872
A large flock of
seagulls got lost in a fog,

1045
01:23:10,951 --> 01:23:13,579
and headed into the town
where all the lights were.

1046
01:23:13,687 --> 01:23:16,952
They made some mess, too,
smashing into buildings and everything.

1047
01:23:16,990 --> 01:23:21,484
They always make a mess. The point is
that no one seemed to be upset about it.

1048
01:23:21,561 --> 01:23:24,997
They were all gone next morning, just
as though nothing at all had happened.

1049
01:23:25,098 --> 01:23:28,363
- Poor things.
- I'm leaving! Are you coming?

1050
01:23:28,401 --> 01:23:30,369
All right, all right!

1051
01:23:32,506 --> 01:23:34,872
Well, hope you folks
figure this thing out!

1052
01:23:34,975 --> 01:23:37,773
It's the end of the world!

1053
01:23:37,878 --> 01:23:40,574
I better get back to the
cannery. What do I owe you, Deke?

1054
01:23:40,680 --> 01:23:41,634
S- Sebastian, hold it a minute. Huh?

1055
01:23:42,491 --> 01:23:43,987
I- I don't want to be an alarmist,

1056
01:23:44,100 --> 01:23:45,596
but... No one ever said you were

1057
01:23:45,708 --> 01:23:48,450
I think we're in real trouble. I
don't know how this started, or why,

1058
01:23:48,557 --> 01:23:50,830
but I know it's here and
we'd be crazy to ignore it.

1059
01:23:50,871 --> 01:23:53,784
To ignore what? The "bird
war"? Yes, the "bird war. "

1060
01:23:53,887 --> 01:23:55,920
The bird attack,
plague... Call it what you like,

1061
01:23:55,999 --> 01:23:58,307
they're massing out there
someplace, and they'll be back.

1062
01:23:58,412 --> 01:24:01,325
Ridiculous. C- Come here.

1063
01:24:01,430 --> 01:24:02,960
Unless we do something right now,

1064
01:24:03,039 --> 01:24:04,843
unless we get Bodega
Bay on the move, they...

1065
01:24:04,950 --> 01:24:06,892
Look, Mitch.

1066
01:24:06,994 --> 01:24:09,976
Even if... Even if this is
true, even if all the birds...

1067
01:24:10,079 --> 01:24:13,896
Don't you believe it's
true? No, Mitch, frankly I don't.

1068
01:24:13,933 --> 01:24:17,109
There's no reason I... Well,
it's happening. Isn't that a reason?

1069
01:24:17,219 --> 01:24:19,755
I like Bodega Bay as well as
the next man... Fine, then help me.

1070
01:24:19,867 --> 01:24:22,140
You're an important man.
If you help, they all will.

1071
01:24:22,179 --> 01:24:24,383
Help how? What do you want to do?

1072
01:24:24,492 --> 01:24:26,468
Mrs. Bundy said
something about Santa Cruz.

1073
01:24:26,571 --> 01:24:29,381
About seagulls getting lost in a
fog and flying in towards the lights.

1074
01:24:29,419 --> 01:24:31,727
We don't have fog this
time of year! Make our own fog!

1075
01:24:31,800 --> 01:24:33,398
How do you figure to do that? We can use

1076
01:24:33,510 --> 01:24:35,040
smoke pots, the way the Army uses them.

1077
01:24:35,152 --> 01:24:38,626
Look!

1078
01:24:38,673 --> 01:24:42,490
They're attacking again.
Melanie, you stay in here. Come on, Al!

1079
01:24:47,120 --> 01:24:49,096
Look out!

1080
01:25:18,027 --> 01:25:21,134
Look at the gas. That
man's lighting a cigar!

1081
01:25:22,820 --> 01:25:25,802
Hey, you! Watch out!
Don't drop that match!

1082
01:25:25,837 --> 01:25:29,048
- Get out of there!
- Mister, run!

1083
01:26:21,415 --> 01:26:23,791
Hey!

1084
01:28:33,491 --> 01:28:37,399
Why are they doing this?

1085
01:28:37,491 --> 01:28:39,480
Why are they doing this?

1086
01:28:39,592 --> 01:28:43,788
They said when you got
here, the whole thing started!

1087
01:28:46,631 --> 01:28:50,087
Who are you? What are you?

1088
01:28:50,199 --> 01:28:52,392
Where did you come from?

1089
01:28:53,534 --> 01:28:56,729
I think you're the cause of all this.

1090
01:28:56,837 --> 01:28:59,236
I think you're evil! Evil!

1091
01:29:01,840 --> 01:29:03,829
Oh, God!

1092
01:29:08,145 --> 01:29:10,976
I think they're going!

1093
01:29:11,048 --> 01:29:13,037
We can get Cathy at Annie's now.

1094
01:29:46,872 --> 01:29:49,169
The crows again. Shh!

1095
01:29:54,076 --> 01:29:56,065
Come on.

1096
01:30:25,898 --> 01:30:29,889
Oh, no. Stay here. S
- Stay here.

1097
01:30:37,605 --> 01:30:40,902
Cathy! Where's Cathy?

1098
01:31:12,664 --> 01:31:14,961
Mitch, don't!

1099
01:31:42,885 --> 01:31:45,681
Oh, don't leave her there, Mitch.

1100
01:31:55,160 --> 01:31:57,525
Oh!

1101
01:32:48,296 --> 01:32:50,262
Come on.

1102
01:32:51,298 --> 01:32:54,163
Shh.

1103
01:33:21,019 --> 01:33:24,453
Wh-When we got back
from taking Michele home...

1104
01:33:27,123 --> 01:33:29,749
we-we heard the explosion and we went...

1105
01:33:29,825 --> 01:33:32,417
we went outside to see what it was.

1106
01:33:32,526 --> 01:33:37,223
All-All at once the...
the birds were everywhere!

1107
01:33:37,262 --> 01:33:40,626
All at once she pushed me inside...

1108
01:33:40,731 --> 01:33:42,629
and they covered her!

1109
01:33:42,733 --> 01:33:46,428
Annie... She pushed me inside!

1110
01:34:01,913 --> 01:34:03,879
Give me another one, darling.

1111
01:34:10,886 --> 01:34:12,784
How long have they been gathering there?

1112
01:34:12,887 --> 01:34:14,785
Oh, about 15 minutes.

1113
01:34:19,625 --> 01:34:21,591
Seems like a pattern, doesn't it?

1114
01:34:23,394 --> 01:34:26,828
They strike, then disappear,
and then start massing again.

1115
01:34:35,236 --> 01:34:37,703
Doesn't look so very different, does it?

1116
01:34:37,804 --> 01:34:40,032
A little smoke hanging
over the town, otherwise...

1117
01:34:41,440 --> 01:34:43,599
You want to try your father again?

1118
01:34:43,708 --> 01:34:46,005
No, I tried a little
while ago. The phone's dead.

1119
01:34:46,042 --> 01:34:48,600
Still got power, haven't we? Yes.

1120
01:34:48,712 --> 01:34:51,611
Mitch, I'm getting
something on the radio.

1121
01:34:51,714 --> 01:34:53,737
Come on.

1122
01:34:58,752 --> 01:35:01,947
I can't get any of the local stations.

1123
01:35:01,988 --> 01:35:03,977
I think this is San Francisco.

1124
01:35:04,055 --> 01:35:07,580
"...and the work of a team
of professionals. " End quote.

1125
01:35:07,658 --> 01:35:10,148
In Bodega Bay early this
morning, a large flock of crows...

1126
01:35:10,194 --> 01:35:13,684
attacked a group of children who were
leaving the school during a fire drill.

1127
01:35:13,762 --> 01:35:17,252
One little girl was seriously injured
and taken to the hospital in Santa Rosa,

1128
01:35:17,365 --> 01:35:19,593
but the majority of
children reached safety.

1129
01:35:19,699 --> 01:35:22,098
We understand there was
another attack on the town,

1130
01:35:22,167 --> 01:35:24,360
but this information is rather sketchy.

1131
01:35:24,470 --> 01:35:26,368
So far, no word has come through...

1132
01:35:26,471 --> 01:35:28,961
to show if there
have been further attacks.

1133
01:35:29,072 --> 01:35:31,562
On the national scene
today, in Washington...

1134
01:35:31,607 --> 01:35:35,166
Well, is that all?

1135
01:35:35,211 --> 01:35:38,303
I'll have to get some more
water. Mustn't let this fire go out.

1136
01:35:38,379 --> 01:35:42,676
Did you get the windows in the
attic, Mitch? Yes, I got 'em all, dear.

1137
01:35:42,715 --> 01:35:44,977
When do you think
they'll come? I don't know.

1138
01:35:45,083 --> 01:35:47,516
If there are bigger birds,
Mitch, they'll get into the house.

1139
01:35:47,585 --> 01:35:50,381
Well, it's just a chance we'll
have to take. Maybe we ought to leave.

1140
01:35:50,421 --> 01:35:52,387
No, not now! Not when
they're massing out there.

1141
01:35:52,489 --> 01:35:54,717
When? W
- We'll just see what happens.

1142
01:35:54,758 --> 01:35:56,315
Where will we go? L

1143
01:35:56,358 --> 01:35:58,723
- I don't know. I think
we're safe here for the time being

1144
01:35:58,760 --> 01:36:01,352
Let's get the wood in now. What
happens when you run out of wood?

1145
01:36:01,462 --> 01:36:04,122
I don't know! We'll break up
the furniture. You don't know!

1146
01:36:04,163 --> 01:36:07,130
You don't know! When will
you know? When we're all dead!

1147
01:36:07,166 --> 01:36:10,725
If only your father were here...

1148
01:36:11,168 --> 01:36:15,364
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Mitch.

1149
01:36:17,373 --> 01:36:19,532
Make yourself some coffee, won't you?

1150
01:36:23,144 --> 01:36:25,269
"In assuming the
tasks of the presidency,

1151
01:36:25,345 --> 01:36:28,073
I said that few generations..."

1152
01:36:33,951 --> 01:36:37,112
Where are they
heading? Somewhere inland.

1153
01:36:37,153 --> 01:36:40,348
Santa Rosa? Maybe.

1154
01:36:40,388 --> 01:36:42,354
Come on. Let's get the wood.

1155
01:37:20,316 --> 01:37:23,909
Mitch? Can I bring
the lovebirds in here?

1156
01:37:24,018 --> 01:37:25,507
- No

1157
01:37:25,618 --> 01:37:29,143
But, Mom, they're in a
cage. They're birds, aren't they?

1158
01:37:31,123 --> 01:37:33,613
Let's leave them in
the kitchen, huh, honey?

1159
01:38:21,491 --> 01:38:25,720
Mitch, why are they
doing this, the birds?

1160
01:38:25,794 --> 01:38:29,922
We don't know, honey. Why
are they trying to kill people?

1161
01:38:30,031 --> 01:38:32,088
I wish I could say.

1162
01:39:45,781 --> 01:39:51,114
I- I'm sick, Melanie.

1163
01:39:53,088 --> 01:39:56,486
I want to... I'll go with you.

1164
01:44:31,444 --> 01:44:33,410
They're going.

1165
01:45:45,329 --> 01:45:48,228
Mitch?

1166
01:48:47,053 --> 01:48:49,611
Oh, Mitch!

1167
01:49:06,866 --> 01:49:09,560
Melanie! Melanie!

1168
01:49:55,533 --> 01:49:58,897
Oh, poor thing! Poor thing!

1169
01:49:58,935 --> 01:50:01,232
Listen, get some water,
bandages and antiseptic. Quickly!

1170
01:50:01,303 --> 01:50:03,634
Bandages. It's terrible.

1171
01:50:07,709 --> 01:50:09,698
Cathy, get some brandy.

1172
01:50:20,950 --> 01:50:23,610
No, no, no! No, no, it's all right.

1173
01:50:23,720 --> 01:50:25,709
No, it's all right, it's
all right, it's all right.

1174
01:50:25,821 --> 01:50:28,845
It's all right. It's all right. No.

1175
01:50:28,922 --> 01:50:32,913
No. Shh! Shh!

1176
01:50:56,775 --> 01:50:58,673
Cathy, get the lamp.

1177
01:51:13,386 --> 01:51:15,614
We've got to get her to a hospital.

1178
01:51:15,688 --> 01:51:18,587
We can't, Mitch. There's no
place we can go. There's San Francisco.

1179
01:51:18,623 --> 01:51:21,022
We'd never make it. We have to try.

1180
01:51:21,091 --> 01:51:24,183
We'll go by way of Bay Hill Road.
Then we don't have to go through town.

1181
01:51:24,294 --> 01:51:26,192
We can't stay here. She needs help!

1182
01:51:26,296 --> 01:51:30,993
I'm frightened. Terribly frightened.

1183
01:51:31,098 --> 01:51:34,190
I don't know what's outside there.

1184
01:51:34,302 --> 01:51:37,326
We better get started
before another attack comes.

1185
01:51:37,437 --> 01:51:40,495
We'll take Melanie's car.
That'll be faster than the truck.

1186
01:51:40,605 --> 01:51:42,798
Can you finish the bandaging? I'll try.

1187
01:51:42,906 --> 01:51:44,804
All right.

1188
01:51:51,146 --> 01:51:55,671
Mitch? See if you can get
anything on the car radio.

1189
01:53:54,431 --> 01:53:56,989
The bird attacks have
subsided for the time being.

1190
01:53:57,098 --> 01:53:59,588
Bodega Bay seems to be the
center, though there are reports...

1191
01:53:59,633 --> 01:54:03,533
of minor attacks on
Sebastopol and a few on Santa Rosa.

1192
01:54:03,604 --> 01:54:06,094
Bodega Bay has been
cordoned off by roadblocks.

1193
01:54:06,205 --> 01:54:08,137
Most of the townspeople
have managed to get out,

1194
01:54:08,206 --> 01:54:11,105
but there are still some
isolated pockets of people.

1195
01:54:11,208 --> 01:54:14,606
No decision has been arrived at
yet as to what the next step will be,

1196
01:54:14,644 --> 01:54:17,805
but there's been some discussion as
to whether the military should go in.

1197
01:54:17,913 --> 01:54:21,608
It appears that the bird attacks come
in waves, with long intervals between.

1198
01:54:21,649 --> 01:54:25,310
The reason for this
does not seem clear as yet.

1199
01:56:15,660 --> 01:56:17,683
Did you hear anything on the radio?

1200
01:56:17,762 --> 01:56:20,285
It's-lt's all right. Come on.

1201
01:56:58,656 --> 01:57:01,123
No. No!

1202
01:57:01,159 --> 01:57:03,125
Shh. Shh.

1203
01:57:30,278 --> 01:57:33,676
- Mitch?
- Shh!

1204
01:57:33,747 --> 01:57:35,770
Stay there.

1205
01:57:43,153 --> 01:57:45,484
Can I bring the lovebirds, Mitch?

1206
01:57:45,555 --> 01:57:47,783
They haven't harmed anyone.

1207
01:57:47,891 --> 01:57:50,153
A- All right. Bring them.

